result.execSummary:
The defendant Kory G Danielson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation/extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.
Defendant shall not enter any establishments where the primary purpose is the sale/service of alcohol.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent.

Defendant shall participate in an AODA assessment and treatment.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

Defendant shall submit to random screens of his blood, breath, or urine.
